(202, 1, '2013-05-24 12:06:17', '2013-05-24 16:06:17', '<img class="size-medium wp-image-203 alignleft" title="chasing excellence memorial day" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/8324/files/2013/05/usa-memorial-day-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />Memorial Day is a time to take stock of the present, reflect on the past, and renew our commitment to the future.  Ronald Reagan\n\nEvery new day brings opportunities and challenges, possibilities and problems, victories and defeats. We tackle them with our full strength and creativity, but only because we are free to work them out in our own way. And, President Regan said we owe this freedom of choice and action to those men and women in uniform who have served and continue to serve this nation and its interest.\n\nThink about the many topics weve covered on Chasing Excellence. Hard Work, Commitment, Focus, Enthusiasm, Trust, Honesty, Cooperation and others all apply to how far our country has come, and hopefully apply to how far weve come in our personal and professional lives.\n\nChasing Excellence will be back next week with a new video message, but today we encourage you to heed President Reagans advice. Take the time to think about where you are now, where you want to be and what you will do to get there.\n\nEnjoy your weekend!', 'Never Stop Chasing Excellence', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'never-stop-chasing-excellence', '', '', '2013-05-24 12:06:17', '2013-05-24 16:06:17', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=202', 0, 'post', '', 0),
