(213, 1, '2013-06-03 03:00:12', '2013-06-03 07:00:12', '<a href="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/8324/files/2013/05/the_palms_2_480.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-214 alignleft" title="the_palms_2_480" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/8324/files/2013/05/the_palms_2_480-300x201.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="201" /></a>Im headed to Las Vegas this week for MasterMind 2013. Will you be there too? If so, Id love to see you!\n\nIve gathered a number of industry experts, including Frank Garay and Brian Stevens from the National Real Estate Post, Dave Savage from the Mortgage Coach and Barry Habib from MBS Highway, for a special pre-MasterMind event. If youre free, please join us Tuesday, June 4 at 2 p.m. in the Madison Ballroom of the Palms Hotel.\n\nIm also excited to be a panelist on MasterMinds Power Lunch / Executive Roundtable Thursday, June 6 from 12:30 to 2 p.m. Participate in this session for industry insight from a diverse panel, and stop by to say hello after!\n\nRick', 'Viva Las Vegas!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'viva-las-vegas', '', '', '2013-06-03 03:00:12', '2013-06-03 07:00:12', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=213', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2013-06-07 18:58:59', '2013-06-07 22:58:59', '<a href="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/8324/files/2013/06/MM2013.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-221 alignleft" title="Rick Floyd Mastermind 2013" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/8324/files/2013/06/MM2013-300x204.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="204" /></a>This week I had the pleasure of attending MasterMind 2013 in Las Vegas. It was amazing to see more than 2,500 mortgage professionals truly passionate about building or simply re-energizing their business. Attendees shared a hunger to be better, a desire to do more and a drive to make it happen. In short, attendees were Chasing Excellence.\n\nI wanted to take a few minutes to share some of my takeaways from the event:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Frank Garay</strong> and Brian <strong>Stevens</strong> spoke on commitment. Having a focus, a task, a vision and seeing it through. <strong>Commitment.</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Barry Habib</strong> spoke on perseverance. We may get knocked down, but we wont get knocked out. <strong>Perseverance.</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Greg Frost</strong>, the mortgage industrys first billion-dollar originator, spoke on being an authority. Being an authority is better than being in authority. Delivering messages of value works every time. <strong>Authority.</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Rick Ruby</strong>, a national coach for top lenders and realtors, challenged us to have a list of five income-producing goals each day. Write them down and cross them off. <strong>Goals.</strong></li>\n	<li>And the highlight of the event was three hours with the incomparable <strong>Tony Robbins</strong>. I could write a book on all of my takeaways from Tony, but this point really stuck out: success is 80% psychology and 20% strategy. Mindset, beliefs and emotion outweigh the specific steps needed to accomplish the result. <strong>Psychology.</strong></li>\n</ul>\nOne REMN Loan Originator that attended the event said, I wish we could bottle this stuff up and take a sip of it every day so that we can carry the enthusiasm forward. I think this is a great point. No matter your industry, consider attending two or three events like this year to help you stay focused, stay motivated and continue on your quest to Chase Excellence.\n\nAlso, one Chasing Excellence programming note. Many of you have provided great feedback on my weekly videos. One piece of advice that I continue to hear is that I should send the videos out earlier in the week. So, starting next week Chasing Excellence will go out every Tuesday.\n\nThanks for your support and interest! Have a great weekend!', 'Stay Focused. Stay Motivated. Chase Excellence.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'stay-focused-stay-motivated-chase-excellence', '', '', '2013-06-07 18:58:59', '2013-06-07 22:58:59', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=220', 0, 'post', '', 1),
