(502, 1, '2014-03-11 06:35:23', '2014-03-11 10:35:23', '<iframe name="wistia_embed" src="//fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/tchcwziusb?videoFoam=true" height="360" width="640" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><script type="text/javascript" src="//fast.wistia.net/assets/external/iframe-api-v1.js"></script>\r\n\r\nThis week on Chasing Excellence Rick Floyd introduces us to Zig Ziglar''s book ''Selling 101''. Find out how to fall in love with your sales career! As salespeople we can sometimes fall out of love with our profession. But on today''s video Rick reminds us of how wonderful a career in sales is from chapter one of Selling 101.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/selling-101-zig-ziglar/1100189793?ean=9780785264811" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-506" alt="Selling 101" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Selling-101-9780785264811-216x300.jpg" width="142" height="198" /></a>Zig Ziglar has a wonderful way of laying out the skills we need in order to become great sales people and he does it in such a way that you become motivated and revived. This first chapter of Selling 101 truly testifies to this fact. There are many reasons we love being salespeople. Think of the income you can earn, they time you have and the flexibility. Most people simply don''t have this type of experiences where they work, but you do.\r\n\r\nSo you can fall in love with sales again, you just need a reminder. Be sure to watch today''s show and share it with anyone you feel could use it. And remember you can always request a transcript of today''s show for your own marketing by filling out the form to your right!\r\n\r\nHave a great day!\r\n\r\nRick', 'Falling In Love With Your Sales Career', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'falling-in-love-with-your-sales-career', '', '', '2014-03-11 10:12:47', '2014-03-11 14:12:47', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=502', 0, 'post', '', 0),
