(516, 1, '2014-03-25 06:00:55', '2014-03-25 10:00:55', 'We all know that a salesperson that can make us laugh is enjoyable to work with. But what if you don''t think you''re funny?\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/d5obm9ahog?videoFoam=true" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" class="wistia_embed" name="wistia_embed" allowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen webkitallowfullscreen oallowfullscreen msallowfullscreen width="640" height="360"></iframe><script src="//fast.wistia.net/assets/external/iframe-api-v1.js"></script>\r\n\r\nIn this week''s show Rick goes over Jeffrey Gitomer''s Little Red Book of Selling principle 8. In this chapter Jeffrey goes over how humor can really make a big difference when it comes to sales. All things being equal a salesperson that can make a prospective customer laugh has a much higher chance of closing the deal then one who can''t.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Little-Red-Book-Selling-Principles/dp/1885167601" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-511" alt="Little Red Book" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Little-Red-Book.jpg" width="128" height="192" /></a>But hey, not everybody is a comedian right? Maybe that''s you. But have you considered what you can do about it? Be sure to tune into today''s show. In just a couple minutes Rick will give you some tips based on Jeffrey''s book that can get you going in the right direction. So push play, you''ll be glad you did. And leave us your comments because we can all benefit from them!\r\n\r\nHave a great productive week Chasing Excellence!\r\n\r\nRick Floyd', 'Learning How to Increase Sales with Humor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'learning-how-to-increase-sales-with-humor', '', '', '2014-03-25 04:14:57', '2014-03-25 08:14:57', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=516', 0, 'post', '', 0),
