(653, 1, '2014-09-16 08:29:23', '2014-09-16 12:29:23', '<iframe name="wistia_embed" src="//fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/mkknpjqqys?videoFoam=true" height="360" width="640" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><script type="text/javascript" src="//fast.wistia.net/assets/external/iframe-api-v1.js"></script>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/coach-wooden-pyramid-rick-floyd-blog.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-558" alt="coach wooden pyramid rick floyd blog" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/coach-wooden-pyramid-rick-floyd-blog-193x300.jpg" width="193" height="300" /></a>This weeks episode of Chasing Excellence covers chapter 15 of Coach Woodens Pyramid of Success. Join Rick Floyd as he discusses what Coach Wooden meant when he said we should strive for <em>Competitive Greatness.</em>\r\n\r\nAs head coach at UCLA <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Wooden" target="_blank">John Wooden</a> won ten NCAA national championships in a 12-year periodseven in a row  an unprecedented feat. Any coach will tell you that preparation leads to confidence, but Coach Wooden knew that it takes more than just confidence to achieve success.\r\n\r\nTune in to this weeks show and discover how you can achieve <em>Competitive Greatness</em>! Please remember to share your thoughts in the comments section below.\r\n\r\nHave an excellent week!\r\n\r\nRick Floyd', 'Achieving Competitive Greatness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'achieving-competitive-greatness', '', '', '2014-09-16 04:35:21', '2014-09-16 08:35:21', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=653', 0, 'post', '', 0),
