(858, 1, '2015-09-22 06:35:19', '2015-09-22 10:35:19', '<div class="wistia_responsive_padding" style="padding: 56.25% 0 0 0; position: relative;">\r\n<div class="wistia_responsive_wrapper" style="height: 100%; left: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; width: 100%;"><iframe name="wistia_embed" src="//fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/xoee8ym42q?videoFoam=true" height="100%" width="100%" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="//fast.wistia.net/assets/external/E-v1.js" async=""></script>\r\n<a href="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/coach-wooden-pyramid-rick-floyd-blog.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-558" alt="coach wooden pyramid rick floyd blog" src="http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/coach-wooden-pyramid-rick-floyd-blog-193x300.jpg" width="193" height="300" /></a>This weeks episode of Chasing Excellence covers the Mortar Quality called ''Fight'' in Coach Woodens Pyramid of Success. Join Rick Floyd as he discusses how the intensity of your fight can up your game in both your career and your personal life.\r\n\r\nAs head coach at UCLA, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Wooden" target="_blank">John Wooden</a> won ten NCAA national championships in a 12-year periodseven in a row  an unprecedented feat. Todays video reveals one of the keys to his success. So press play and get ready to crank up that fire in your belly!\r\n\r\nI encourage you to share this video on facebook and other social media sites! Also, please remember to share your own thoughts in the comments section below.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHave an excellent week!\r\n\r\nRick Floyd', 'How Intense Is Your ''Fight''?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-intense-is-your-fight', '', '', '2015-09-22 01:18:51', '2015-09-22 05:18:51', '', 0, 'http://chasingexcellenceblog.com/?p=858', 0, 'post', '', 0),
